@startuml
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
'
' Objective-side runtime flow of the standalone /mdd-deploy utility
' skill. Guidance-only: it writes artifacts and a runbook then STOPS;
' it never executes a deployment command.
'
' CHANGE (this cycle): a mandatory IaC-dialect resolution + BLOCKING
' confirmation step is inserted BEFORE any artifact is written. No
' silent default — an unspecified/unconfirmed dialect halts the skill
' before diagram.puml / generated IaC / runbook.md exist. The generated
' IaC step is now dialect-aware (Bicep XOR Terraform) with full
' invariant + secure-by-default parity between the two.
'
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "How /mdd-deploy turns a one-line description into deployment guidance: validate target=azure-container-apps, read MDD models + the target repo read-only, STOP for a blocking clarification on ambiguity OR a statically detectable go-live landmine, then RESOLVE the IaC dialect and BLOCK for explicit operator confirmation (Bicep XOR Terraform; no silent default) before writing anything, write the deployment diagram, generate secure-by-default IaC in the confirmed dialect (Bicep: infra/main.bicep+modules; Terraform: infra/main.tf+modules+azurerm provider+remote state backend) enforcing the identical invariant checklist, write the STOP-gated runbook, then report and execute nothing.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "How /mdd-render rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to its deterministic .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg mirror so the deployment diagram is inspectable like every other diagram. Additive, non-gating.")
title /mdd-deploy guidance and inspection (objective)

actor "Operator" as Op
participant "/mdd-deploy\n(utility skill)" as Dep
participant ".mdd/models/\ncomponents + use-cases" as Models
participant "../atlas-ate-server\n(target repo, read-only)" as Target
database ".mdd/deploy/\nazure-container-apps/" as Store
participant "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/ (generated IaC)" as Infra
participant "/mdd-render" as Render
database ".mdd/rendered/deploy/" as Rendered

== SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE ==
Op -> Dep : /mdd-deploy <deployment description>
alt target != azure-container-apps
  Dep --> Op : not yet supported (v1 = azure-container-apps only); stop
else target == azure-container-apps
  Dep -> Models : read components + use-cases (the "what")
  Dep -> Target : read README, Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml,\n.env.example, src (READ-ONLY)
  opt topology/security choice ambiguous OR a go-live landmine is statically detectable
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING clarification (same discipline as /mdd-cycle)
    Op --> Dep : decision
  end

  group MANDATORY dialect confirmation — BEFORE any artifact (USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
    Dep -> Dep : resolve requested IaC dialect from the description\n(Bicep | Terraform) — exactly one; NO silent default
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm: "generate <dialect> IaC?"\n(unspecified/unconfirmed -> STOP, write nothing)
    Op --> Dep : confirmed dialect
    note right of Dep
      No deploy artifact (diagram.puml, generated IaC,
      runbook.md) is written until the dialect is
      explicitly confirmed. Same blocking discipline as
      the landmine pause; never a buried STOP note.
    end note
  end

  Dep -> Store : write diagram.puml (UML deployment diagram;\ndocumentation-only security stereotypes)
  alt confirmed dialect == Bicep
    Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.bicep (+ modules)
  else confirmed dialect == Terraform
    Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.tf (+ modules):\nazurerm provider + remote state backend
  end
  note right of Infra
    FULL PARITY regardless of dialect: Container Apps,
    ACR, Azure DB for PostgreSQL (TLS), Key Vault
    (Deny + bypass=AzureServices when peers private),
    secret refs, ingress 8080, pre-traffic migration
    job. No store left more network-open than its
    peers — auto-hardened, not deferred.
  end note
  Dep -> Store : write runbook.md (numbered steps; exact command,\nlocation, env/secret; STOP before every state-changing\nor go-live step incl. the billing production gate)
  note right of Dep
    Enforces every atlas-ate-server invariant identically
    for either dialect: Key-Vault-only secrets, App
    Attest required, billing production multi-factor
    gate, BYOK never touches the server, DB TLS +
    at-rest, pre-traffic migration job, non-root,
    port 8080. Caveat: migrations-before-traffic stays
    procedural (documented v1 tradeoff, not auto-changed).
  end note
  Dep --> Op : report written files; review the diagram\nand run the runbook yourself. Executes NOTHING.
end

== SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT ==
Op -> Render : /mdd-render
Render -> Store : read .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml
Render -> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg\n(deterministic mirror; additive, non-gating)
Render --> Op : rendered SVG list

note over Store
  .mdd/deploy/ is an inspection artifact only.
  /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the /mdd-cycle
  parity loop never read it.
end note
@enduml
